Class StringCacheKeyGenerator

All Implemented Interfaces:
CacheKeyGenerator<String>
public class StringCacheKeyGenerator
extends AbstractCacheKeyGenerator<String>

Uses Arrays.deepToString(Object[]) to generate a cache key. This is a decent compromise on using ListCacheKeyGenerator if all arguments implement toString well since hashCode and equals operations on the generated key are much faster than on the List returned by ListCacheKeyGenerator and the chance of key collision is very small for objects with a well implemented toString.

Pros Cons
Faster both for key generation and key comparison than ListCacheKeyGenerator. Depends on all arguments implementing toString well enough to represent each argument's identity.
Arguments do not have to implement Serializable
